Preheat the oven to 220C/425F/Gas 7.Brush an ovenproof dish with melted butter and then coat with the grated chocolate.Place the strawberries into a food processor and blend until smooth. Transfer to a bowl and stir in the sugar and egg yolks.In a separate bowl, whisk the egg whites until stiff then fold into the strawberry mixture.Pour the mixture into the dish and place in the oven and bake for 8-10 minutes, or until well risen and golden.Remove from the oven and dust with icing sugar to serve.